<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The four pointer initializations (conn_record = NULL; sock_record = NULL; sock = NULL; conn = NULL;) are redundant. All four variables are assigned (via OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET and related code) before any use in every execution path where they are actually dereferenced; if OS_ObjectIdGetById fails the variables are never used. Therefore removing these initializations would not change program behaviour, so they constitute dead code (present only to appease static analysis).
</scenario>
